<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Almighty Jones Defeated at World Cup Athletics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, September 13 (Xinhua) -- Marion Jones, the
U.S.sprint sensation, tasted her first loss in this season of
athletic events when she was beaten by German legend Heike
Drechsler in the long jump Sunday afternoon at the IAAF World Cup
in Athletics in Johannesburg.
</P>
<P>
She jumped 7.00m while Drechsler jumped 7.07m on the third and
final day of the quadrennial track and field showpiece. The
7.00m she achieved was by no means great for Jones compared with
her personal best of 7.31m set earlier this year.
</P>
<P>
Braving drizzle and chilly wind, Drechsler, 33, proved her
class as the reigning European champion and snatched the gold
from the U.S.favorite.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Guan Yingnan won the first bronze for the Asian
women's team at the World Cup with a jump of 6.74m. The
20-year-old Asian champion added much needed 6 points to her
contingent, which was ranked last but one on the standings.
</P>
</TEXT>
