<HEADLINE> Thailand Eleven Remains in Asian Games Draw </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, September 14 (Xinhua) -- Hosts Thailand's national
soccer squad remained in the Asian Games draw despite being
suspended from international events, officials said on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Thai team received the suspension for a farcical match
against Indonesia which sparked calls for a crackdown on soccer
corruption.
</P>
<P>
But officials, who announced the draw for the Asian Games,
confirmed only the pull-out of Indonesia's soccer team along with
Malaysia and Saudi Arabia.
</P>
<P>
Deputy Prime Minister Bhichai Rattakul said Thailand had
learned the lesson from the shameful Tiger Cup match in Vietnam
in August.
</P>
<P>
"We got a painful lesson and we learnt a hard way," he
said."the Thai team was young and should move on from past
failures."
</P>
<P>
Bhichai said that he had received a very good response from
officials of the Asian Football Confederation (AFC).
</P>
<P>
The AFC suspended both teams Friday over a match that they
played to lose and called for a task force to tackle resurgent
soccer corruption.
</P>
<P>
"It is a good time for Thailand to erase the shameful match in
Vietnam," he added.
</P>
<P>
Bhichai said 27 countries and regions would send football
teams to the Asian Games, the biggest entry in the history of the
tournament. 
</P>
</TEXT>
