<HEADLINE> China to Launch First Charity Website on Internet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 14 (Xinhua) -- China's first charity auction
website will be available on the Internet on September 23.
</P>
<P>
The website, jointly established by the China Charity
Foundation (CCF), Beijing Municipal Telegraph Bureau and Wisdom
Science and Technology Enterprise, will be used to collect funds
for China's flooded areas from sales of the works of Chinese
painters and calligraphers, as well as items provided by antique
collectors.
</P>
<P>
The website can accessed via two addresses ---
www.china-charity.org and www.chinacharity.cn.net. Related
information will be available at the e-mail
address: info.china-charity.org.
</P>
<P>
The CCF will use funds raised from the auctions to set up a
charity fund for China's flood victims.
</P>
<P>
Serious flooding, which hit central, eastern and northeastern
parts of China this summer, caused massive economic losses. The
CCF has donated 470 million yuan (57 million US dollars) to the
flood relief effort.  
</P>
</TEXT>
