<HEADLINE> Shenyang Exports More Machinery, Electronic Goods </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, September 14 (Xinhua) -- This capital of northeast
China's Liaoning Province has exported more machinery and
electronic products this year, official statistics show.
</P>
<P>
Shenyang exported nearly 100 million US dollars-worth of such
items in the first seven months of this year, 14.7 percent more
than in the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
Shenyang has, over recent years, taken various effective
measures to promote exports of machinery and electronic products
as a way to rejuvenate its state-owned enterprises, a local
official said.
</P>
<P>
Priority has been given to equipment for power transmission,
mining facilities, equipment for power stations and equipment for
road construction, among others, the official said.
</P>
<P>
Shenyang is a major industrial city in northeast China.
</P>
