<HEADLINE> Three Trophies Going to China, One at Stake </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 14 (Xinhua) -- China showed their dominance
as they were on the road of taking at least three titles with
only one trophy at stake after Monday's grenade throwing in the
CISM 46th Military Pentathlon World Championships here.
</P>
<P>
With a total of 12,808.2 points, the Chinese women's team now
lead their closest rivals Denmark by 412.5 points. Sweden are
third with another 135.6 points behind the host team.
</P>
<P>
Four-time champion Wang Lianying now leads the individual
standings with 4,397.6 points, followed by her three teammates in
the second to fourth places.
</P>
<P>
As for the men's team event, China collected a total of
17,712.7 points after they won the grenade throwing, leading
second-placed Brazil by 362.7 points.
</P>
<P>
"It's impossible for us to catch up with China," Brazil's
coach Helcio Botelho said.
</P>
<P>
China's Yang Chunyi, who finished second with 128 hits and
66.8 meters in grenade throwing events, now leads the individual
standings with 4,448.6 points.
</P>
<P>
Another Chinese athlete Guo Xinqiao came second with just 5.4
points behind. His compatriot Li Zhong is third with 4,420.9
points.
</P>
<P>
Defending champion Carlos Silva of Brazil is in the seventh
place with 4,369.2 points. He still has the chance to win the
individual title as he is very strong in the cross country
running, the last event of the individual competitions.
</P>
<P>
"I think Silva will beat Guo in tomorrow's running," said
Botelho. "But other Chinese athletes are also good runners."
</P>
