<HEADLINE> Swaziland, S. Africa to Scrap Double Taxation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, September 14 (Xinhua) -- Swaziland is soon to
reach an agreement to scrap double taxation on goods imported
from -- and exported to -- South Africa, Mauritius and The United
States, a senior Swazi official said Monday.
</P>
<P>
The present system of double taxation on goods and earnings
was discouraging potential new investors, South African Press
Association quoted outgoing Swazi Finance Minister Themba Masuku
as saying.
</P>
<P>
However, Masuku declined to say when the agreement would be
signed.
</P>
<P>
Swaziland, bordering with South Africa and Mozambique, is a
member state of the Southern African Development Community.
