<HEADLINE> Philippines to Crack Down on Gambling Activities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, September 14 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Joseph
Estrada Monday ordered the police to crack down hard on gambling
operations nationwide and arrest and file criminal charges against
gambling lords.
</P>
<P>
In a memorandum to National Police Director Roberto Lastimoso,
Estrada specifically ordered the arrest and indictment of the
gambling lords who have been using their supposed "connections"
with the president to peddle gambling activities.
</P>
<P>
Estrada ordered Lastimoso to stop "decisively and without
compromise" all illegal forms of gambling that are now rampant
especially in central and southern Philippines.
</P>
<P>
The president said his office has received reports that certain
individuals "have been using supposed connections with me or my
office to promote these activities."
</P>
<P>
"If true, you are hereby directed to find those individuals,
arrest them, and file the necessary criminal charges," Estrada
told the police chief.
</P>
<P>
The president ordered Lastimoso to comply swiftly with his
orders and report to him on a regular basis all developments on
the government's anti-gambling campaign. 
</P>
