<BODY>
<HEADLINE> State Launches Inspection of Amusement Rides </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 14 (Xinhua) -- The State Quality and
Technology Supervision Bureau has issued a circular on the
carrying out of quality inspection on all the rides in amusement
parks and other places across the country.
</P>
<P>
The inspection is aimed at guarding against and preventing
accidents caused by such rides because of quality problems and the
poor management of amusement parks, the circular said.
</P>
<P>
Since the beginning of this year, a number of such accidents
have taken place, causing the loss of both lives and property. In
an extreme case, which took place in Zhabei Park in Shanghai City
on August 30, one person was killed and eight others injured.
</P>
<P>
The State Quality Inspection Center of Amusement Rides and the
quality and technology supervision departments at provincial
levels are required to launch inspection on both the production
and sales of rides, and shut down enterprises without safety
certificates, the circular said.
</P>
<P>
The rides and other facilities in amusement parks which have
been found to have safety problems and have been repaired, should
pass inspection by quality and technology departments at
provincial levels before they are allowed to re-start operations.
</P>
<P>
Rides which are beyond repair should be scrapped, according to
the circular.
</P>
<P>
The quality and technology supervision departments across the
country are to report the results of the inspection to the State
Quality and Technology Supervision Bureau by the end of October.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
