<HEADLINE> Zambia to Attract More Overseas Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, September 14 (Xinhua) -- Zambian Vice-President
Christon Tembo said that the government is reviewing the
country's investment incentives to attract more overseas
investment.
</P>
<P>
When launching the Freelander Land Rover made by Britain on
the Zambian market in Lusaka at the weekend, Tembo said that the
Zambian government would soon bring together people who have
invested in the country to discuss their problems in order to
come up with lasting solutions, Times of Zambia reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
"We as government will continue to review the existing
investment incentives with a view to improving upon them so as to
attract more foreign investment," Tembo said.
</P>
<P>
He appealed to international investors to come and invest in
Zambia, adding that the Zambian government would remain committed
to improving investment incentives in all sectors of the economy.
</P>
<P>
Zambia, which Liberalized its economy in early 1990s, is now
an ideal investment destination in the southern Africa for
foreigners due to its stable political situation and free foreign
exchange, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
