<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Judiciary Shake-Up Successful (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Xiao Yang said the courts discovered 14,993 wrong judgements in
respect to the application of law in cases self-examined in the
first eight months this year, and in re-examined already-concluded
trials. They have corrected 8,110 wrong verdicts, and the others
are being addressed according to law, he said.
</P>
<P>
Prosecutors also found 1,454 mishandled litigations out of a
total of nearly 50,000 criminal lawsuits, and have corrected 1,255
of them, top-prosecutor Han said.
</P>
<P>
Both courts and prosecutorial offices opened hotlines to
solicit public reports on illegal activities by their
employees. Courts received over 12,000 reports in the first eight
months this year, placed nearly 5,000 judges on file for
investigation, judged 4,701 of them guilty, and had 131 punished
as criminal offenders.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, prosecutorial offices put 1,337 prosecutors under
investigation, concluded the examination of 777 of them,
disciplined 756, and brought legal proceedings against 73.
</P>
<P>
While affirming the results of the rectification movement, both
Xiao and Han admitted that they "cannot overestimate the
achievements and many problems should not be ignored." For
instance, some courts or procuratorates have treated this
rectification movement as only a formality; some deep rooted
problems are left untouched; judicial leaders have done little to
expose themselves and many blame objective conditions instead of
themselves for the spread illegal practices.
</P>
<P>
Both Xiao and Han said they will further their efforts in
uncovering and punishing illegal practices in their own
departments. Han said that this work is an important criterion for
the shake-up movement.
</P>
<P>
All the other specific measures required for the movement
will also be enforced, they said, to maintain the dignity and
unity of the law and ensure justice for the ultimate goal of
maintaining social stability and contributing to the country's
reform, opening up and economic development.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
