<HEADLINE> China, Japan Hold Talks on Asian Financial Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 14 (Xinhua) -- China and Japan held talks
here today on the Asian financial crisis and other economic issues
of common concern.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese officials attending the talks were from the
Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation (MOFTEC), the
Foreign Ministry, the State Development Planning Commission, the
Finance Ministry and the People's Bank of China.
</P>
<P>
The Japanese delegation included senior officials from Japan's
Foreign Affairs Ministry, Ministry of International Trade and
Industry, Economic Planning Agency, Finance Ministry and its
embassy in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The two sides exchanged views on the Asian economy, bilateral
and multilateral economic relations, and countermeasures against
the lingering Asian financial crisis.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Vice-Minister of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation
Sun Guangxiang and Japanese Deputy Foreign Minister Koichi
Haraguchi hosted the discussion.  
</P>
</TEXT>
