<DOCNO> XIE19980914.0084 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kenya to Host World Forum on Securities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, September 14 (Xinhua) -- More than 600 regulators of
capital markets from over 60 countries will meet in Nairobi from
Wednesday to Friday this week over "the serious challenges facing
financial markets at the turn of the century."
</P>
<P>
It will bring together 134 worldwide regulatory agencies that
are members of the International Organization of Securities
Commissions (IOSCO). This is the first IOSCO conference in Africa.
</P>
<P>
Paul Melly, the chief of Kenya's Capital Markets Authority
(CMA) which is the host to the 23rd annual IOSCO conference, said
the meeting is to deliberate and adopt the Principles of
Securities Regulations, a landmark document that sets out the
objectives of securities regulation.
</P>
<P>
The document seeks ways to give guidance to governments,
market regulators, international agencies and private consultants
to guarantee the smooth operation of securities markets.
</P>
<P>
"We will work on the framework that will facilitate the co-
ordination of the markets all over the world," the CMA boss said
in a news release.
</P>
<P>
He said the meeting will also come up with international
disclosure on guidelines and standards for cross-border offering
and initial listing by foreign issuers of stock.
</P>
<P>
These standards are expected to serve as useful guidelines for
facilitating cross-border issuance and listings of financial
securities and will highlight basic required non-financial
disclosure requirements.
</P>
<P>
The conference will also serve as a useful forum for the top
financial regulators worldwide to share ideas and experiences as
well as discuss issues of mutual interest in financial markets
development and regulation.
</P>
<P>
Other topics to be covered at the conference will include
cross-border investment flows and the stability and development
of markets, international cooperation in the investigation and
enforcement of securities laws and so on.
</P>
<P>
Delegates from the World Bank, International Finance
Cooperation, International Monetary Fund and the U.N. Industrial
and Development Organization will also attend the meeting.
</P>
<P>
IOSCO, formed 23 years ago, meets annually to discuss issues
related to world securities and futures markets.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
