<HEADLINE> International Symposium Explores Central Asia Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, September 14 (Xinhua) -- The second international
symposium on sustainable development in Central Asia, which opened
here today has drawn more than 100 scholars and experts from 20
countries and regions.
</P>
<P>
With the theme of regional development in Central Asia's arid
plains and mountainous areas, the participants will discuss and
exchange views on such issues as sustainable utilization of land,
soil erosion control, protection of water resources, bio-diversity
and the utilization of regenerative energies.
</P>
<P>
Launched by the Council for Sustainable Development of Central
Asia, the symposium was first held in 1994, in Ulan Bator, capital
of Mongolia.  
</P>
</TEXT>
