<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Guangzhou Hosts Int'l Packaging Show </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 14 (Xinhua) -- The '98 China International
Packaging Show convened in this capital city of south China's
Guangdong Province today.
</P>
<P>
More than 250 companies from Australia, Italy, Belgium,
Denmark, the Netherlands, Finland and about a dozen other
countries and regions participated in the show, displaying their
latest packaging machinery, materials, finished products and
testing equipment.
</P>
<P>
The four-day show is jointly sponsored by the China General
Packaging Corporation, the China Packaging Technology Association
and Hong Kong's Miller Freeman Asia Ltd.
</P>
<P>
China's packaging industry has developed rapidly since the
country adopted its reform and open policy in the late 1970s, with
the total output value in this sector surging from seven billion
yuan (843 million U.S. dollars) in 1980 to 176 billion yuan in
1996.  
</P>
</TEXT>
