<DOCNO> XIE19980914.0087 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> German Exports to South America Surge 13.2 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, September 14 (Xinhua) -- Germany's exports to South
American countries soared 13.2 percent in the first half of this
year to a total of 8.7 billion marks (5.1 billion U.S. dollars),
the German Federal Statistics Office said Monday.
</P>
<P>
The growth in exports to South America coincides with an eight
percent fall in exports to Asia to 46.5 billion marks (27.1
billion dollars), mainly due to the Asian financial crisis, the
statistics office said earlier.
</P>
<P>
The data issued by the Wiesbaden-based office on Monday also put
German imports from South America in the first half year at 6.4
billion marks (3.7 billion dollars), up 4.4 percent from the same
period last year.
</P>
<P>
For 1997 as a whole, German exports to South America increased
by 22.4 percent to 17.1 billion marks (10 billion dollars) while
imports from the region rose 18.1 percent to 13 billion marks (7.6
billion dollars). 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
