<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Contemporary Hong Kong Art Biennial Exhibition 1998 Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 14 (Xinhua) -- An exhibition featuring art
works by local artists of Chinese paintings and calligraphys,
print, sculpture and ceramics opened here Monday.
</P>
<P>
Art works of news media such as photograph and mixed media are
also displayed in Contemporary Hong Kong Art Biennial exhibition
1998.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the opening ceremony, Mok Ying-fan, chairman of the
Provisional Urban Council's Museums Select Committee, said that
the diversity of art styles in the exhibition is reflective of the
recent artistic pursuit and the achievement of Hong Kong artists.
</P>
<P>
Mok said that there are works reflecting the characteristic of
Hong Kong as well as works inherited from tradition yet rich in
contemporary spirit, displaying the diversity of Hong Kong
culture, and reflecting Hong Kong as a cosmopolitan city
influenced by East and West.
</P>
<P>
"As the 12th Biennial this year, it carries an aim to promote
Hong Kong art and stimulate general awareness of and interest in
art in Hong Kong," Mok said.
</P>
<P>
It also serves to encourage more local artists to participate
in artistic creation and develop their artistic talents, he said.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition, which will be open to the public at the Museum
of Art's Special Exhibition Gallery from now to October 11,
comprises some 100 works of art selected from over 1,000 entries
based on originality, creativity and technical competence.
</P>
</TEXT>
