<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-14 13:29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Khamenei Calls on Islamic World to Rescue Afghan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, September 14 (Xinhua) -- Iran's supreme leader
Ayatollah Ali Khamenei Monday called on the Islamic countries and
world Muslims to rescue the oppressed nation of Afghanistan,
Tehran radio reported.
</P>
<P>
Khamenei made the call in a strong-worded statement issued here
following the conquer of the Afghan Taliban militia on Bamyan,
the center of Afghan Shiite Muslims in northern Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
"I call on all the governments of the Muslim countries, the
freedom-loving nations of the Islamic world to rescue the
oppressed Afghan people from the Taliban's massacre," he said.
</P>
<P>
He also urged the Pakistani people not to allow the Pakistani
soldiers to participate in the massacre of millions of Afghan
people and to prevent the religious war in Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
The criminal actions committed by the Taliban in Mazari
Sharif, northern Afghanistan with massacre of civilians and the
Iranian diplomats and correspondent, obligated the Muslim nations
around the world to take a decisive action against the savage
group, he said.
</P>
<P>
The Taliban announced on Thursday that they found the bodies of
nine of the 11 missing Iranian diplomats. Iran later confirmed
the death of the nine diplomats and the reporter, but said that
two others escaped the Taliban's massacre.
</P>
<P>
Local observers believed that the strong-worded statement
indicated a quite possibility for Iran to take measures against
the Taliban, as senior Iranian officials repeatedly announced to
take revenge on the Taliban for killing Iranian diplomats.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
