<HEADLINE> Shandong Province Sets Up Ocean Research Institute </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, September 14 (Xinhua) -- East China's Shandong Province
today set up an ocean research institute in the coastal city of
Qingdao in a bid to make its advantages in oceanographic studies
serve the economic growth better.
</P>
<P>
Shao Guifang, deputy governor of Shandong, said the institute
will mainly shoulder the tasks of organizing major oceanographic
development projects, offering consultancy to local governments,
building a key laboratory for oceanographic studies and
oceanographic information network, in addition to fostering
leading researchers in the field.
</P>
<P>
Shandong has now nearly 200 institutions specializing in
oceanographic studies and teaching, with a total staff of more
than 2,000, said Shao.
</P>
<P>
In 1991, Shandong put forward the strategy of developing the
ocean through science and technology. The province reaped added
value totalling 36.6 billion yuan (about 4.4 billion U.S. dollars)
from its marine industry last year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
