<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, September 14 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the
Kuala Lumpur Stock Exchange (KLSE) closed higher Monday on support
from local institutions in the second half of the afternoon
session.
</P>
<P>
The market Monday opened firm but immediately succumbed to
profit taking by mostly retail players. This scenario continued up
to mid afternoon.
</P>
<P>
However, following this strong buying support was seen,
absorbing all the selling pressures.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stock composite index rose 6.71
percent or 24.71 points to close at 393.24, the all-share Emas
index rose 5.85 points to 102.48, the industrial index added 41.58
points to 752.19 and second board index was 2.06 points higher at
92.83.
</P>
<P>
Gainers led losers by 503 to 154, while 86 counters were
unchanged, 179 others untraded and 39 suspended.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover amounted to 232.525 million shares worth
308.096 million ringgit (about 81.077 million U.S. dollars) from
last Friday's 181.876 million shares valued at 268.673 million
ringgit (about 70.703 million dollars).
</P>
<P>
The main board turnover increased to 224.087 million shares
worth 296.092 million ringgit (about 77.918 million dollars) from
175.093 million shares valued at 258.281 million ringgit (about
67.968 million dollars) last Friday.
</P>
<P>
The second board index rose to 8.438 million shares worth
12.004 million ringgit (about 3.158 million dollars) from 6.783
million shares valued at 10.392 million ringgit (about 2.734
million dollars) last Friday.
</P>
<P>
Off market turnover, however, fell to 889,800 shares worth
5.326 million ringgit (about 1.401 million dollars) from last
Friday's 6.655 million shares valued at 9.518 million ringgit
(about 2.504 million dollars). 
</P>
