<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nepali Opposition Blocks House Session Over Crucial </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, September 14 (Xinhua) -- The Nepal's main opposition
party Monday disrupted the proceedings in the Lower House of
Parliament for the fourth day over a crucial bill.
</P>
<P>
Immediately after the session started in the House, MPs of the
Communist Party of Nepal (United Marxism-Leninism, CPN-UML)
shouted slogans in protest against the Local Autonomy Bill.
</P>
<P>
They demanded a provision which automatically terminates one's
post if a local elected-official defects to other parties be added
into the bill, which was tabled in parliament last week.
</P>
<P>
The party fears that if the bill is passed, thousands of local
party workers may defect to its rival group, the Communist Party
of Nepal (Marxism-Leninism, CPN-ML), which broke away from it in
March this year and joined the minority government of the Nepali
Congress (NC) late last month.
</P>
<P>
Most of the mayors, deputy mayors, district development
committee chairmen, vice chairmen and members elected from the
CPN-UML during the local elections in May and July last year have
joined the CPN-ML. Thus their political future hinges on the bill.
</P>
<P>
More local elected-members are said to be wishful to join the
CPN-ML, but are waiting for the bill to be passed in parliament.
</P>
<P>
Observers here noted that the CPN-ML aimed to get the bill
passed in parliament in order to win over more workers for the
next general elections due to be held before November 1999.
</P>
<P>
With a comfortable majority of 128 seats in the 205-member
house, the NC and the CPN-ML can easily get the bill passed.
</P>
<P>
The bill had been approved by an overwhelming majority of votes
in the Parliamentary Committee on Development before being
presented to the House for discussion and vote.
</P>
<P>
But CPN-UML MPs say that the bill is against the norms of the
multi-party democracy and should be returned to the parliamentary
committee for further discussion. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
