<HEADLINE> ARATS Urges Political Dialogue With Taiwan Counterpart </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 15 (Xinhua) -- The Beijing-based Association
for Relations Across the Straits (ARATS) has urged political
dialogue with its counterpart in Taiwan as the prelude to possible
political talks between the two sides.
</P>
<P>
In a letter sent Monday to the Strait Exchange Foundation (SEF)
in Taiwan, ARATS expressed appreciation for recent remarks by some
people in Taiwan about political talks between the two sides.
</P>
<P>
"We hope ARATS and SEF will conduct political dialogue at the
earlist possible date, and thereby make arrangements for
procedural talks prior to political talks across the straits," the
letter said.
</P>
<P>
The letter reiterated the principles for political talks
expounded in late August by officials in charge of Taiwan Affairs
in the Central Committee of the Chinese Communist Party and the
State Council which said that talks should first be focused on
"officially terminating hostilities across the straits under the
principle of one China".
</P>
<P>
ARATS and SEF should first exchange views on procedural
arrangements for political talks and then resume economic and
business talks, the officials suggested. 
</P>
