<HEADLINE> HK's External Trade in July Decreases </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 14 (Xinhua) -- The value of re-exports in
Hong Kong in July 1998 decreased by 13 percent over a year earlier
to 100.9 billion HK dollars (12.94 billion U.S. dollars),
according to figures released by the Census and Statistics
Department of Hong Kong Monday.
</P>
<P>
The volume of domestic exports in July this year decreased by
10 percent to 18.2 billion HK dollars (2.33 billion U.S. dollars)
and the value of imports decreased by 18 percent to 123.1 billion
HK dollars (15.78 billion U.S. dollars), according to the figures.
</P>
<P>
Comparing July 1998 with July 1997, decreases were recorded in
the value of re-exports to Singapore (31 percent), Taiwan (24
percent), Japan (23 percent), the Chinese mainland (15 percent),
Germany (14 percent), the United States (7.6 percent) and the
Netherlands (6.2 percent).
</P>
<P>
Nevertheless, increases were recorded in the value of
re-exports to France (5.8 percent), Canada (3.3 percent) and the
United Kingdom (2.2 percent).
</P>
<P>
Taking all destinations together, the value of re-exports in
the first seven months of 1998, at 666.9 billion HK dollars (85.5
billion U.S. dollars), was 3.5 percent lower than that in the same
period in 1997. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
