<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-14 12:24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tanzanian Vice President in Kuwait to Boost Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, September 14 (Xinhua) -- Tanzanian Vice President
Omari Ali Juma arrived here Monday morning to boost bilateral
ties, the KUNA news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Kuwaiti Crown Prince and Prime Minister Sheikh Saad Al-Abdullah
Al-Salem Al-Sabah greeted Juma at Kuwait City's international
airport.
</P>
<P>
During his three-stay, Juma will hold talks with senior Kuwaiti
officials and businessmen on "bilateral ties and means of
enhancing them in various domains," the agency said.
</P>
<P>
Tanzania, among the African countries to condemn Iraqi invasion
of Kuwait in 1990, has repeatedly said it supported Kuwait's just
cause and called on Iraq to implement all relevant U.N.
resolutions.
</P>
<P>
Bilateral ties between Tanzania and Kuwait have warmed up since
1992 with increaseed exchange of visits by senior officials
between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Kuwait has financed 10 projects in Tanzania with an investment
of at least 155 million U.S. dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
