<HEADLINE> Shanghai Opens First Container Shipping Line to Southern Japan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, September 14 (Xinhua) -- The port of Shanghai today
opened an international container shipping line to southern parts
of Japan which will connect with all other ports there.
</P>
<P>
The regular shipping line will be in operation two weeks a
month, in every middle and last ten-day period of a month.
</P>
<P>
The shipping line, coordinated by the Longwu Loading and
Unloading Company of Shanghai and the Sino-Asia Lines of Hong
Kong, will greatly improve the container transport network of the
port of Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Since it opened the first domestic container shipping line in
December 1996, the Longwu Loading and Unloading Company of
Shanghai has become the country's container transport hub for
domestic trade, with a handling capacity of 56,000 TEU containers
in the January-August period.  
</P>
