<HEADLINE> China's First High-Speed Railway Line </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The railway line will link Beijing and Shanghai, and the
train's speed will exceed 200 kilometers per hour. A number of
countries are in bidding competition to provide rails for the
construction of the line.
</P>
<P>
Scientists and technicians from the Panzhihua Steel
Corporation, the country's largest manufacturer of railway tracks,
located in southwest China's Sichuan Province, will join in the
competition, sources said.
</P>
<P>
"We are hoping that the new railway line will use domestic-made
rails," said Hong Jibi, president of the corporation. He revealed
that the corporation has the capability of making high-speed rails
of equal quality to foreign-made ones.
</P>
<P>
In 1994, China opened a 160-kilometer-per-hour railway line
between Guangzhou and Shenzhen, and the rails for this line were
produced by Hong's corporation.
</P>
<P>
Hong said his corporation has increased investment in its
high-speed rail program and is preparing for large-scale
production.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
