<HEADLINE> DPRK: Man-Made Satellite Works Well </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PYONGYANG, September 14 (Xinhua) -- The man-made satellite of
the Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK), which was
launched into space last month, works very well, according to an
article published in the newspaper Rodong Sinmun Monday.
</P>
<P>
The satellite, named "Kwangmyongsong No.1," made its 100th
circle around the earth between 08:24 and 11:17 local time (2017
GMT) on September 13, the article said.
</P>
<P>
Scientists of the DPRK had observed the satellite when it was
passing the country in the sky.
</P>
<P>
The satellite is expected to be seen with naked eyes when it is
passing the DPRK in early October, they said. 
</P>
