<HEADLINE> Wu Yi Urges Expanded Anti-smuggling Efforts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, September 14 (Xinhua) -- China is determined to crack
down on major smuggling cases as quickly and effectively as
possible.
</P>
<P>
Wu Yi, an alternate member of the Political Bureau of the
Communist Party of China (CPC) Central Committee, made the remark
during a recent fact-finding tour of east China's Fujian
Province.
</P>
<P>
She pointed out the CPC Central Committee and State Council
have paid close attention to the anti-smuggling campaign which has
an important bearing on the fulfillment of this year's economic
growth target and will ensure the continued success of China's
reform, opening and modernization efforts.
</P>
<P>
Wu, who also serves as a State Councillor, said relevant
departments and regions should strengthen cooperation and improve
efficiency to battle smuggling involving large sums of money.
</P>
<P>
She stressed that departments and individuals found guilty of
smuggling will be subject to harsh punishment.
</P>
<P>
Wu visited the Xiamen and Fuzhou Customs departments during her
six-day tour and stressed the need for honest and highly trained
customs officials.  
</P>
</TEXT>
