<HEADLINE> Jakarta Students Rally to Protest Against Price Hikes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, September 14 (Xinhua) -- Hundreds of students staged a
peaceful rally in front of the House of Representatives here
Monday, urging the government to reduce the prices of staple food.
</P>
<P>
"Prices (of commodities) continue to soar and there is no
indication that they will decrease soon," head of the Student
Movement of the Indonesian Muslim Preaching Academy Jamaluddin
Effendi said.
</P>
<P>
In a statement read by Effendi, the group demanded that the
House urge the government to settle the misuse of funds as well as
bring to justice staple food "jockeys" who have made the people
suffer.
</P>
<P>
The demonstrators dispersed at noon, and traffic continued to
flow as usual despite the rally.
</P>
<P>
Last week, students in Jakarta, Surabaya, Semarang, Bandung and
other cities held rallies to protest the spiraling prices of the
basic commodities. They urged President B. J. Habibie to take
concrete measures to solve the economic crisis.
</P>
<P>
Over the past couple of weeks, rice prices have sharply
increased to about 5,000 rupiah (0.45 U.S. dollar) per kilogram,
compared to the Indonesian government's targeted price of 2,000
rupiah per kilogram. 
</P>
</TEXT>
