<HEADLINE> Heavy Fighting Occurs in Border Town of Congo (K) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 14 (Xinhua) -- A heavy fighting broke out
early Monday morning in the eastern border town of Goma of the
Democratic Republic of Congo, AFP reported.
</P>
<P>
The main fighting, which lasted some six hours after taking
place at 3:00 a.m. (local time), appeared to be in the center of
Goma, the eastern headquarters of the rebels, and the town's
airport. Rifle fires were still going on in some areas, the report
said.
</P>
<P>
So far, no specific attackers were identified. "We don't
know" who is attacking, Ernest Wamba dia Wamba, the rebels'
political leader, was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
However, some sources said that the attackers included Rwandan
Hutus -- former soldiers and militiamen defeated by Tutsi rebels
in Rwanda's 1994 civil war, according to the report. 
</P>
</TEXT>
