<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese, Irish Prime Ministers Hold Talks in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 14 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji
and his Irish counterpart Bertie Ahern held talks in the Great
Hall of the People here this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
They are expected to exchange views on a wide range of issues
of shared interest. At press time, the talks are still going on.
</P>
<P>
Prior to the talks, Zhu hosted a welcoming ceremony to greet
his Irish counterpart. After the talks, Zhu is scheduled to give a
dinner in honor of Ahern.
</P>
<P>
Ahern, who arrived here earlier today for a five-day official
visit as Zhu's guest, is the first Irish prime minister visiting
China since the two countries forged diplomatic relations in 1979.
</P>
<P>
During his stay in Beijing, Ahern is scheduled to meet with
Chinese President Jiang Zemin. He will also visit Shanghai and the
Hong Kong Special Administrative Region.  
</P>
</TEXT>
