<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Share Prices Close Sharply Higher in Tokyo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, September 14 (Xinhua) -- Stock prices closed sharply
higher on Monday in Tokyo as investors rushed to buy stocks
following news reports that the ruling Liberal Democratic Party
(LDP) submitted a new compromise plan for financial reform.
</P>
<P>
The Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected issues on the First
Section of the Tokyo Stock Exchange advanced 310.39 points, or
2.23 percent, from last Friday's finish to end at 14,227.37.
</P>
<P>
The broader-based Tokyo Stock Price Index (TOPIX), covering all
First Section issues, rose 12.68 points or 1.18 percent to
1,084.16.
</P>
<P>
Turnover on the major section came to an estimated 350 million
shares, well down from this year's record 1.25 billion shares
traded on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Long-Term Credit Bank of Japan was the day's most heavily
traded issue.
</P>
<P>
Tokyo shares gained a big boost in early afternoon trading on
news reports that the LDP submitted a new compromise plan for
financial reform which includes stricter criteria for using public
funds to aid troubled banks.
</P>
<P>
The reports sent the price of Nikkei index future contracts
soaring, and investors rushed to buy stocks mainly to fill
arbitrage positions.
</P>
<P>
Of the 1,341 issues listed on the First Section, gainers
outnumbered losers 792 to 358, with 151 issues remaining
unchanged. 
</P>
</TEXT>
