<HEADLINE> Hould-Marchand Takes Solo Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, September 14 (Xinhua) -- Canada's Valerie
Hould-Marchand clinched the gold medal in the synchronised
swimming solo event on Monday at the Commonwealth Games.
</P>
<P>
The 18-year-old, who perfomred to "Romeo and Juliet", won the
title with a combined 93.640 points.
</P>
<P>
"I'm very happy to win the gold medal. It was quite tough
because everything has to be perfect," Hould-Marchand said.
</P>
<P>
Hould-Marchand also won the technical routine, the first part
of the event, on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Australian Naomi Young took the silver with 90.933 points,
England's Gayle Adamson was third with 87.564 points.  
</P>
</TEXT>
