<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bierhoff Voted German Footballer of the Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, September 14 (Xinhua) -- AC Milan striker Oliver
Bierhoff was voted German Footballer of the Year by a panel of
sports journalists, local reports said here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The 30-year-old Bierhoff beat veteran Bayern Munich libero
Lothar Matthaeus and Kaiserslautern striker Olaf Marschall into
second and third places in the vote.
</P>
<P>
Bierhoff was the top scorer in the Italian Serie A last season
with 27 goals for Udinese. He then moved to AC Milan and scored
twice in a 3-0 win over Bologna in the club's opening league
match last Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Bierhoff won 501 votes compared with 196 for Matthaeus and 107
for Marschall. Borussia Dortmund defender Juergen Kohler, who
claimed the award last year, came fifth. 
</P>
</TEXT>
