<HEADLINE> China Enjoys Booming Border Trade With Russia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HOHHOT, September 14 (Xinhua) -- The trade volume at land ports
along the Sino-Russian border surged 20 percent to 260 million US
dollars by the end of June this year, according to a report
released today by the Manzhouli Customs House of Inner Mongolia.
</P>
<P>
Imports grew by 21 on the 1997 period to 240 million US
dollars, with exports rising 11 percent to 14 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
China's trade deficit with Russia grew slightly to 230 million
US dollars.
</P>
<P>
State-owned enterprises led the nation in terms of related
imports and exports, with said ventures accounting for 99 percent
of the trade volume for small ticket items. Principal export
items included farm and side-line products, with paper pulp, raw
plastics and other low tariff commodities accounting for the
majority of imports.  
</P>
</TEXT>
