<HEADLINE> Pak Imports Down in 1st 2 Months of Current Fiscal Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, September 14 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan's imports during
the first two months of the current fiscal year (July 1-June 30 )
declined by 17.21 percent when compared with the same period of
last fiscal year.
</P>
<P>
According to the provisional figures released Monday by the
Federal Bureau of Statistics, the imports decrease is mainly due
to decline in the import of food items and petroleum products.
</P>
<P>
The figures show that the imports in July and August amounted
to 1.402 billion U.S. dollars as against 1.694 billion dollars in
the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
The decline in the petroleum group is 46.68 percent and that in
the food group is 38.36 percent. Meanwhile, the import in the
machinery group also recorded a decline of 18.68 percent.
</P>
<P>
However, the imports in the agricultural and other chemical
group registered an increase of 20.58 percent when compared with
the corresponding period of last year.
</P>
<P>
There was a major decline in the import of petroleum products
which recorded 123.26 million dollars in the first two months of
the current fiscal year while the import of petroleum products in
the same period of last fiscal year was 231 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
The upward movement in imports of agricultural group was mainly
due to the increase in the fertilizer import which amounted to
11.31 million dollars in July and August as against 200,000
dollars in the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
The trade deficit in the first two months of this year is 308
million dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
