<HEADLINE> Queen Elizabeth II to Visit Malaysia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, September 14 (Xinhua) -- Queen Elizabeth II will
make a state visit to Malaysia from September 20 to 23.
</P>
<P>
She will be accompanied by the Duke of Edinburgh and Secretary
of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs Robin Cook, said a
statement from the British High Commission here.
</P>
<P>
This will be the Queen's first visit to Malaysia since 1989
when Kuala Lumpur hosted the Commonwealth Heads of Government
Meeting.
</P>
<P>
The statement said the visit reflects the close and friendly
relationship between Britain and Malaysia.
</P>
<P>
"It is also a reflection of Britain's commitment to Malaysia,
especially at this time of economic adversity," it added.
</P>
<P>
While here, the Queen will attend the 16th Commonwealth Games
in her capacity as Head of the Commonwealth and will officially
close the Games on September 21 at the invitation of Malaysian
Supreme Head of State Tuanku Ja'afar who will also host a state
banquet in her honor.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, she will also meet Prime Minister Mahathir
Mohamad.
</P>
<P>
The Duke of Edinburgh will have separate engagements including
a meeting with key players in Malaysia's financial services sector
and a visit to Cyberjaya for a briefing on the Multimedia Super
Corridor (MSC). 
</P>
</TEXT>
