<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Developing Eight (D-8) Summit Postponed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, September 14 (Xinhua) -- The summit of the Developing
Eight (D-8), which was scheduled to be held in Dhaka in the latter
part of November, has been postponed in view of the over
two-month-long devastating floods in Bangladesh, it was learned
Monday from the Ministry of Foreign Affairs.
</P>
<P>
The decision was made at a foreign ministry meeting held Sunday
afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The second D-8 summit has been "shelved" for the time being, a
foreign ministry official said, adding this was one of the ways of
saving "every penny" because funds are needed to carry on relief
work and take up rehabilitation activities.
</P>
<P>
All the member countries are being informed of the government
decision, she said.
</P>
<P>
The D-8, an economic grouping, was launched last year at the
summit held in Turkey in July. Its members are Bangladesh, Egypt,
Iran, Indonesia, Malaysia, Nigeria, Pakistan and Turkey. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
