<DOCNO> XIE19980914.0197 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shenzhen Shoots For 14 Percent Economic Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, September 14 (Xinhua) -- Shenzhen Mayor Li Zibin
today expressed confidence that the city can overcome difficulties
and achieve its economic growth target of 14 percent for the year.
</P>
<P>
Speaking in an exclusive interview with Xinhua, Li said
Shenzhen, China's first special economic zone, has adopted a
series of measures to ensure strong momentum for economic growth
during the latter half of the year, including accelerating the
development of high-tech industries, increasing investments in
fixed assets and expanding exports.
</P>
<P>
Statistics for the January-July period show that Shenzhen's
GDP hit 65.91 billion yuan, up 14 percent on the same period last
year. Investments in fixed assets grew by 17.8 percent to 20.6
billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The city used foreign investments totalling 1.6 billion US
dollars, with foreign trade rising by 1.7 percent to 24.57 billion
US dollars.
</P>
<P>
"Shenzhen adopted 22 measures to support high-tech industries,"
said Li, adding that the State Ministry of Science and Technology
provided the city venture capital of some one billion yuan."
</P>
<P>
He noted that Shenzhen will join the Ministry of Science and
Technology, Ministry of Information Industry, Ministry of Foreign
Trade and Economic Cooperation and Chinese Academy of Social
Sciences in sponsoring a large-scale technology fair in a bid to
transform the city into south China's center for high-tech
industries.
</P>
<P>
He said Shenzhen plans to increase the fixed assets investment
to 50 billion yuan this year, 3.6 billion yuan more than the target
figure set a the beginning of the year. An additional 7.7 billion
yuan will be earmarked for a subway and Shenzhen-Hong Kong
transportation projects.
</P>
<P>
Lin said that the local government will strive to sharpen its
competitive edge and achieve a 10 percent growth rate for
exports.  
</P>
</TEXT>
