<HEADLINE> Nominations for Maldivian Presidential Race Underway </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, September 14 (Xinhua) -- Nominations have started for
presidential elections in the Maldives scheduled for November this
year, according to reports reaching here from Male Monday.
</P>
<P>
Maldivian Elections Commissioner Abdulla Rasheed who has called
for nominations from prospective candidates has given time till
September 19 to file the papers personally to him.
</P>
<P>
Maumoon Abdul Gayoom, as president since 1978, completes his
latest five year term in office on November 10.
</P>
<P>
The reports quoted Maldivian officials as saying that this is
the first time for the Maldives to hold multi-candidate
presidential elections after changing its constitution earlier
this year to make the elections more democratic and transparent.
</P>
<P>
According to the revised electoral procedure, the elections
commissioner will decide whether the candidates who file
nominations will meet the necessary criteria and forward the list
to the Peoples' Majalis (Parliament).
</P>
<P>
The Majalis will select the final candidate by secret ballot
who will then be put to a nationwide vote for election as
president for a term of five years, the reports added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
