<DOCNO> XIE19980914.0225 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Czech Republic Faces Serious Unemployment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, September 13 (Xinhua) -- "Unemployment, like a time
bomb, is exploding in the Czech Republic," claimed Czech Prime
Minister Milos Zeman recently.
</P>
<P>
Unemployment in August this year reached 320,000, a record of
6.4 percent since the country started reforms towards a market
economy in 1990.
</P>
<P>
In some northern parts, the rate rose to as high as 14
percent.
</P>
<P>
However, local economists expect unemployment to continue
increasing in the near future, and expect a rate of 7 percent by
the end of the year, 8.4 percent next year and more than 10
percent by year 2000.
</P>
<P>
Of the eastern European countries, the Czech Republic was once
considered a great success in the economic transition with low
unemployment as well as constant development.
</P>
<P>
In 1995, unemployment rate was only 2.9 percent, one of the
lowest in the world, until the recent serious economic slide
boosted it up.
</P>
<P>
The growth rate of Czech's gross national product (GDP) in the
same year reached 6.4 percent. But, it began to slow down as the
government relaxed its macro-control of the economy and put too
much premium on the role of the market itself.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, the country saw a GDP growth of only one percent, and
in the first half of this year, a minus 1.8 percent. Estimation
said the country may record a zero growth of economy this year.
</P>
<P>
Under the circumstance, the government was forced to cut down
expenses while many enterprises had to make large numbers of
layoffs, adding to an already rising unemployment figure.
</P>
<P>
Feeling the pain, the Czech government has not worked out
effective measures yet, but Zeman said, it would reform its
employment policy, reduce the taxation on small and medium-sized
enterprises, and encourage foreign investment in the country.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980914.0226 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-14 </DATE_TIME>
