<HEADLINE> Ullrch Out of World Championshi Road Race </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, September 13 (Xinhua) -- Former Tour de France winner
Jan Ullrich said on Sunday he will miss the road race at next
month's world championships in Valkenburg, the Netherlands.
</P>
<P>
The 24-year-old German, who has a minor achilles injury, said
he did not want to take any risks and wanted to focus on
preparing for next year's Tour de France.
</P>
<P>
Ullrich, who rides for the Deutsche Telekom team, became the
first German to won the Tour last year. He was second to Italian
Marco Pantani this year. 
</P>
