<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 4 Killed in Indonesia Road Accident </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, September 14 (Xinhua) -- At least four people were
killed and dozens of others injured when a bus collided with a
pick-up car on Sunday in Serang, about 70 kilometers west of
Jakarta, Antara News Agency reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
The bus heading to Serang from Jakarta was overtaking a city
transport van when the car suddenly appeared from the opposite
direction, making the collision inevitable, it said.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted a bus conductor as saying that the bus
carrying 75 passengers then hit a tree before rolling over as far
as 10 meters into a ravine.
</P>
<P>
At least 30 people were injured, some of them seriously, in the
accident, the report said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
