<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading Philippine Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, September 14 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news
items in leading Philippine newspapers Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Philippine Journal:
</P>
<P>
-- President Joseph Estrada has ordered a fresh crackdown on
syndicates forcing street children -- reportedly being held
captive in four safe houses in Metro Manila -- to beg or peddle
illegal drugs.
</P>
<P>
Today:
</P>
<P>
-- A "flexible" interest-rate policy will remain in place under
the latest agreement between the Central Bank of the Philippines
and the International Monetary Fund to ward off any speculative
attacks on the peso.
</P>
<P>
The Business Daily:
</P>
<P>
-- In view of the current regional turmoil, the technical
working group of the Philippine government's Economic Mobilization
Group has directed the commission on tariff and related matters to
review the possibility of slowing down the country's tariff
reduction program. 
</P>
