<HEADLINE> Riis to Stay with Deutsche Telekom </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, September 13 (Xinhua) -- The 1996 Tour de France
winner Bjarn Riis will sign a new contract with his Deutsche
Telekom team, a team spokesman announced here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The 34-year-old Dane, who did not start the Tour of Spain at
the beginning of September, is set to go to Copenhagen on Tuesday
to meet the team sporting director Walter Godefroot of Belgium to
settle the deal. 
</P>
</TEXT>
